&lt;comment&gt; Review comments in XML for commentary here (schema is not parsing HTML formatting inside comment tag) 


        Not sure if/how we want to communicate functional package guidance but this is our expectation for what claims can be made:
        &lt;br/&gt;
        TLS package:&lt;br/&gt;
        - TLS with mutual authentication is mandatory&lt;br/&gt;
        - DTLS with mutual authentication is optional&lt;br/&gt;
        Any other requirements can be specified freely&lt;br/&gt;
        FTP_ITC_EXT.1 doesn't currently specify client vs server but it's implied from context throughout the PP that only client is used
        &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;

        X.509 package:&lt;br/&gt;
        - FIA_XCU_EXT.2 must be claimed because the PP requires support for mutual authentication&lt;br/&gt;
        - the old PP specified PKCS10 and EST as objective requirements for obtaining certificates -
        with the new FP, FIA_X509_EXT.6 is selected because of FIA_XCU_EXT.2 claims (because the TOE will not have its own internal/embedded CA) but there is nothing forcing the specific enrollment method to be used. Right now this means any of PKCS10, EST, CMC, or CMP must be used. If the idea is to only permit PKCS10/EST, some way of communicating that must be applied.&lt;br/&gt;
        - FIA_X509_EXT.1 must be claimed (it was mandatory in the old PP). CRL or OCSP is expected as the only supported revocation methods. Specific additional guidance may be needed to limit the FIA_X509_EXT.1.3 selections to those values. SME input is needed as to whether any of the other selections in this component are mandatory or forbidden.&lt;br/&gt;
        - FIA_X509_EXT.2 must be claimed (it was mandatory in the old PP)&lt;br/&gt;

        Also, right now we don't make an explicit statement in FAU_GEN.1 that the corresponding audit events from the claimed functional package SFRs must also be added to the audit table. Do we need that or is it sufficiently implied? 

      &lt;/comment&gt;      

The scope of this Protection Profile (PP) is to describe the security functionality of mobile devices in terms of [CC] and to define functional and assurance requirements for such devices.

536c2dac-17c4-4bea-bd25-dfaf5ce26e27.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
		All DEKs shall be &lt;assignable&gt;generation mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt; with entropy corresponding
		to the security strength of AES key sizes of 256 bits.
	    &lt;/title&gt;

55055e59-9773-48ef-b668-ee5b9c1baeea.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall provide a mechanism for applications to request the TSF to perform
                the following cryptographic operations: 
                &lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic operations defined by the TSF in FCS_COP.1&lt;/assignable&gt;
                by keys stored in the secure key storage. &lt;/title&gt;

2d3d57bd-8d01-4371-83d2-009425d24697.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall provide
		&lt;assignable&gt;storage medium&lt;/assignable&gt;
		secure key storage for asymmetric private keys and
		&lt;assignable&gt;list of secrets&lt;/assignable&gt;
		.&lt;/title&gt;

a1d33c95-6ce9-4dd6-b569-8fedc367a790.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall allow only the application that imported the key or secret to request
                that the key or secret be destroyed. Exceptions may only be explicitly authorized by
		&lt;assignable&gt;list of subjects&lt;/assignable&gt;.&lt;/title&gt;

b73b0137-75cd-47a0-bc06-e6a0b695a59c.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
		The TSF shall encrypt all DEKs, KEKs, &lt;assignable&gt;any long-term trusted channel
                key material&lt;/assignable&gt; and
		&lt;assignable&gt;other secrets&lt;/assignable&gt;
		by KEKs that are 
		&lt;assignable&gt;protection mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
	      &lt;/title&gt;

d6b6f12e-b452-4e5d-b0fb-6cff09353e82.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;Encryption shall be performed using DEKs with AES in the
	      &lt;assignable&gt;list of AES modes&lt;/assignable&gt; mode with key size
	      &lt;assignable&gt;list of acceptable key sizes&lt;/assignable&gt; bits. &lt;/title&gt;

f030e4ab-15a8-439d-9442-f365f659a28d.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall consider password and
	      &lt;assignable&gt;list of acceptable authentication mechanisms&lt;/assignable&gt;
	      as critical authentication mechanisms. &lt;/title&gt;

ac4a6fcc-fec0-4f9a-84a0-6b206ba4a4c2.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
                The TSF shall be capable of performing &lt;assignable&gt;list of management functions&lt;/assignable&gt;.
              &lt;/title&gt;

note.note:
		    The assignment in function &lt;xref to="mf-serverProtocols"/&gt;
              consists of all protocols where the TSF acts as a server, which can be enabled and
              disabled by either the user or administrator.

		    Function &lt;xref to="mf-certValidity"/&gt; must be
              included in the ST if "administrator is allowed to configure certificate acceptance" is selected in
              FIA_X509_EXT.2.2 in &lt;xref to="pkg-x509"/&gt;

Function &lt;xref to="mf-keyWipeRules"/&gt; should be included in the selection if
&lt;xref to="s-killkey-user"/&gt; or &lt;xref to="s-killkey-admin"/&gt;
is selected in FCS_STG_EXT.1.5.
&lt;rule id="r-killkey-user-mf"&gt;&lt;if&gt;&lt;ref-id&gt;s-killkey-user&lt;/ref-id&gt;&lt;/if&gt;&lt;then&gt;&lt;ref-id&gt;mf-keyWipeRules&lt;/ref-id&gt;&lt;/then&gt;&lt;/rule&gt;&lt;rule id="r-killkey-admin-mf"&gt;&lt;if&gt;&lt;ref-id&gt;s-killkey-admin&lt;/ref-id&gt;&lt;/if&gt;&lt;then&gt;&lt;ref-id&gt;mf-keyWipeRules&lt;/ref-id&gt;&lt;/then&gt;&lt;/rule&gt;

f026fa03-22d7-4a0e-a4e5-e3d6bc8536b1.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
	      The TSF shall offer &lt;assignable&gt;list of remediation actions&lt;/assignable&gt;
	      upon unenrollment and
	      &lt;assignable&gt;list of triggers&lt;/assignable&gt;.&lt;/title&gt;

c8829c0c-d4e3-4a7a-bed4-307b88475194.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
	      The TSF shall &lt;assignable&gt;list access control mechanisms&lt;/assignable&gt; to JTAG.
	    &lt;/title&gt;

7e7d1db0-a52e-4089-b56e-ad01626a31ff.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall use &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;802.11-2012 in accordance with &lt;assignable&gt;requirements or standards defining implementation of this protocol&lt;/assignable&gt;,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;802.1X in accordance with &lt;assignable&gt;requirements or standards defining implementation of this protocol&lt;/assignable&gt;,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;EAP-TLS in accordance with &lt;assignable&gt;requirements or standards defining implementation of this protocol&lt;/assignable&gt;,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mutually authenticated TLS in accordance with &lt;assignable&gt;requirements or standards defining implementation of this protocol&lt;/assignable&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; and &lt;assignable&gt;other protocols&lt;/assignable&gt; protocols to provide a communication channel between itself and another trusted IT product 
                using certificates as defined in &lt;assignable&gt;requirement or standard defining the use of certificates&lt;/assignable&gt; that is logically distinct from other communication channels, 
                provides assured identification of its end points, protects channel data from disclosure, and detects modification of the channel data. &lt;/title&gt;
